Exploratory Data Analysis

  • Correlation Plot shows that variables are correlated to one another alluding to the idea that PCA might be particularly useful. Along with these correlated relationships, there might be latent relationships as well, lets see if we can use PCA to reduce dimensionality.

  • There are some positive correlations between bar, chocolate, and nougat. We also see some strong negative correlations between bar and fruity, as well as bar and pluribus

  • The scree plot, along with the visuals highlighting explained variance indicates that the first two PCAs can represent most of our data set (~71%).

Below we take a look at some elbow plots to give us an idea of the appropriate amount of clusters needed

  • the above shows that changes in sum of square differences begins to elbow around 3 & 5 clusters, while becoming relatively consistent around 10

We will also leverage brute force calculation to test accuracy as cluster count increases
